         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#fellows1841">
            <p> . . . according to the cession given to him by Menander, son of Menander, the son of Telesphorus, the son of Po- lemo [?], through the archives. In this sarcophagus there is buried 
               Julia Antonia Abascantina, who had been his wife: there shall also be buried Apollonius himself. But another shall not have leave to open, or bury anybody else, except Apollonius, the aforesaid. 
               Since he who acts against this, or attempts it, shall be impious, and cursed, and a grave-robber, and pay besides into the most sacred treasury of our master, the Emperor Caesar, 
               6000 silver denaria, of which one-third part is to be his who institutes proceedings pursuant to this inscription.</p>
         </div>
